22/05/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Members of the anti-corruption office USKOK have detained six people from the town of Split on suspicion of smuggling 360kg of cocaine, media in Croatia reported Friday (May 20th). The drugs from Latin America have been seized in Spain. The operation was carried out in co-operation with police services and prosecutor's offices of several European and Latin American countries. (Index.hr, Srna, Blic - 20/05/11) 
